<section class="wrap about">
  <div class="about__intro">
    <div class="about__text">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="page__title">Hi, I'm Ziyan.</h1>
      <p class="about__lede">
        I'm a software engineer and founder. I like building products end to end,
        from the SwiftUI on the screen to the data model underneath, and I care a
        little too much about the parts users never see.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about__portrait" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="about__portrait-frame">
        <span>Z</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose about__body">
    <p>
      <em>This is placeholder copy. Edit <code>src/about.njk</code> to make it yours.</em>
      I started in iOS development and kept following the stack downward: concurrency,
      system design, serverless backends, and the architecture decisions that decide
      whether a product feels fast or fragile. Lately I've been building a startup of my
      own and writing about what I learn along the way.
    </p>

    <h2>What I care about</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Craft.</strong> Small details compound. The drawer that doesn't jitter, the query that doesn't fan out badly: these are the difference between fine and good.</li>
      <li><strong>Clarity.</strong> Whether it's code or an essay, I'm trying to make a complicated thing feel simple without lying about the complexity.</li>
      <li><strong>Thinking in public.</strong> I write to find out what I believe. The notebook on this site is part of that.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Beyond the keyboard</h2>
    <p>
      Outside of building things, I read and write, often in Chinese, about technology,
      learning, and the occasional argument I can't stop having with myself. You'll find
      that side of me under <a href="/notes-essays/">Notes &amp; Essays</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Say hello</h2>
    <p>
      The best way to reach me is email. I'm always happy to talk about systems design,
      iOS, startups, or a good essay.
    </p>
    <p class="about__contacts">
      {% for s in site.socials %}
        <a class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" href="{{ s.url }}"{% if '://' in s.url %} target="_blank" rel="noopener"{% endif %}>{{ s.label }}</a>
      {% endfor %}
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
